#repost @cottonworldlive 

Cottonworld is opening up new horizons, and this time around, we have put the spotlight on our customers. To celebrate 35 years of Cottonworld, we have brought together the community that helped us grow strong. Our new campaign called ‘It’s My Nature' is created with our customers from all over India, showing them to be comfortable in their own skin, no matter who they are and what they do. They represent our unique and diverse Cottonworld family that we love & cherish. ⁠
⁠
We hope you enjoy the film⁠ as much as we enjoyed making it.⁠

latestPosts.caption:
Meet Mubassirah Khatri @elysians_ajrakh — a remarkable artisan from Ajrakhpur, Kutch, and one of the only female artists practicing the intricate art of Ajrakh.

Showcased recently as part of @designcraft.india x @lakmefashionweek in partnership with @fdci, Mubassirah brings a rare feminine perspective to this centuries-old textile tradition. Mentoring her thought this collection has been a great learning for me. 

A true artist, she begins each piece by sketching by hand, then transfers the design onto fabric using mordants and dyes applied through tubes. She also masterfully uses wooden blocks to create negative space—a technique deeply rooted in Ajrakh craft. 

Artistry, heritage, and innovation—Mubbashirah’s work is a testament to all three.
Shoutout to all the stakeholders that brought this show together @amritasomaiya @aradhana_nagpal @juhi.lakhwani @darshana.gajare @mandycardoz36

latestPosts.caption:
Some of my favourite faces and fits from the recent @rkivecity show @lakmefashionwk x @fdciofficial 
Winner of the @circulardesignchallenge presented by @r.elan.official and @uninindia this collection—titled Reclaim the City—offers a bold alternative to the wasteful systems that define much of today’s fashion: mass production, linear consumption, and a disregard for both material and maker.

This is fashion reimagined—where waste becomes a resource, the burnt is beautiful, and traditional craft is a tool to revive, not replace. A reminder that the future of design isn’t just about what’s new, but how we renew.

Couldn’t be more proud of this incredible team. @ritwikkhannaa @__aaravkhanna_ @harveerrrr madhavbahety @__4ry4____

latestPosts.caption:
Every season @lakmefashionwk presents a thrilling opportunity to take on a show that challenges my limits and inspires me to step beyond my comfort zone. When @mandycardoz36 and @darshana.gajare introduced the idea of an artisan-led show, I was immediately captivated. Let’s bring artisans to the forefront of design. 
Within a week, I found myself on a flight to Kutch, accompanied by my talented partners @aradhana_nagpal and @juhi.lakhwani from @designcraft.india . Located within the stunning Prag Mahal complex in Bhuj, @designcraft.india exclusively showcases creations by artisan designers who have graduated from Soumaiya Kala Vidya. The remarkable artisans I’ve collaborated with are a true testament to the incredible work being done at @somaiya_kala_vidya headed by the charming @amritasomaiya 
Our journey began in the charming village of Mundra, where we had the pleasure of meeting Shakil Bhai from @neel_batik . In India, crafting often runs in families, and Shakil Bhai’s studio embodies this tradition, with his brothers, nephews, uncles, and sons all contributing to their unique creations.
What sets Shakil Bhai apart is his remarkable ability to blend traditional block-printing techniques with an abstract, freehand approach. The result? A stunning fusion of abstract patterns and classic block prints that gives his textiles an unmistakable flair.
We opted for simple silhouettes—saris, kaftans, kurtas, and wrap pants—reflecting styles you’d find at local Kutch shops. But what truly distinguished our designs were the vibrant placement prints and locally inspired styling. The accessories, including face masks and headpieces, were all sourced locally in Kutch (shoutout to @aradhana_nagpal ), complemented by striking statement pieces from @anokheeada . 
Along with supplying textiles Shakil Bhai is also an educator conducting regular workshops where he shares his craft with others and now with this collection he adds designer to his list of achievements and I couldn’t be more proud of him and his team. 
Big thanks you to my team: @taruntaruntarun @ankursinghnitwal  @ambsssssssssssssss 
@iamneerajgaba put together the most beautiful show
HMU: @marianna_mukuchyan
